1. Install Terminal and SSH on Home Assistant
  Go to Settings → Add-ons
  Click Add-on Store (bottom right)
  Search for "Terminal & SSH" (official Home Assistant add-on)
  Click it, then click Install
  Once installed, click Start
  Open the add-on's Web UI (or find it in your sidebar if it added an icon)

2. Install HACS within the terminal
   Run:
  wget -O - https://get.hacs.xyz | bash -

3. Restart Home Assistant
  Once it's back up:
  Settings > Devices & Services → Add Integration
  Search for "HACS"
  Follow the on-screen prompts > it will ask you to authorize via GitHub (this is required; HACS pulls custom integrations from GitHub repos)
  Complete the GitHub authorization flow in the popup/tab it opens

4. Install Unifi UNAS App
  Open HACS
  Click HACS in your left sidebar.
  Go to Integrations tab
  Click Integrations at the top.
  Search for the Unifi UNAS App.
  Install It.

5. After it installs it should automatically direct you to sign in to your UNAS:

(You must enable SSH in UNAS Settings fro this to work)

  Enter:
  Your UNAS Pro's local IP address
  Username: root
  Password: the SSH password you set on the UNAS
  
  Select your device model when prompted
